"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:5.12\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">5.12</span> 標題：鍋、盆、罐、壺（cooking pot, kettle）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： דּוּד</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： dud)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:14\">1SA 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:13\">2CH 35:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:12\">JOB 41:12</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： כִּיּוֹר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： kiyor)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:14\">1SA 2:14</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： כְּלִי</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： kli)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:21\">LEV 6:21</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： סִיר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： sir)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:3\">EXO 16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:3\">EXO 27:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:3\">EXO 38:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:45\">1KI 7:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:38\">2KI 4:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:39\">2KI 4:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:40\">2KI 4:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:41\">2KI 4:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:41\">2KI 4:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:14\">2KI 25:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:11\">2CH 4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:16\">2CH 4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:13\">2CH 35:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:23\">JOB 41:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps58:10\">PSA 58:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps60:10\">PSA 60:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps108:10\">PSA 108:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:6\">ECC 7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:13\">JER 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:18\">JER 52:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:19\">JER 52:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:3\">EZK 11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:7\">EZK 11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:11\">EZK 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:3\">EZK 24:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:6\">EZK 24:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:3\">MIC 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:20\">ZEC 14:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:21\">ZEC 14:21</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： פָּרוּר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： parur)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:8\">NUM 11:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:19\">JDG 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:14\">1SA 2:14</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： צַלַּחַת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： tsalachath)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:13\">2CH 35:13</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： קַלַּחַת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： qalachath)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:14\">1SA 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:3\">MIC 3:3</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： λέβης</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： lebēs)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir13:2\">SIR 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd1:13\">1ES 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc7:3\">2MA 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc8:13\">4MA 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc12:1\">4MA 12:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc18:20\">4MA 18:20</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ξέστης</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： xestēs)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:4\">MRK 7:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： τήγανον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： tēganon)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc7:3\">2MA 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc7:5\">2MA 7:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc8:13\">4MA 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc12:10\">4MA 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc12:19\">4MA 12:19</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： χαλκεῖον, χαλκίον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： chalkeion, chalkion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:4\">MRK 7:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd1:13\">1ES 1:13</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： χύτρα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： chutra)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir13:2\">SIR 13:2</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0485_pot.jpg\" alt=\"陶瓷烹飪鍋和儲藏鍋\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">陶瓷烹飪鍋和儲藏鍋 (© Bukvoed, CC BY 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>鍋是用金屬或燒製陶土做成的一種較深的容器。烹飪時，把鍋裝滿水放在火上，再把食物放在水中煮熟。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>所有文化都知道烹飪用的鍋。翻譯者通常需要區分平底鍋和煮流質食物所用的較深的鍋。這裡討論的是後者。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:14\">1SA 2:14</a> 和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:13\">2CH 35:13</a> 列出了幾種烹飪用具。翻譯者可以使用一個概括性的詞語，而無需為每種用具尋找單獨的譯詞；例如，對於<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:14\">1SA 2:14</a> 中的四種容器，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 和<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 簡單地譯為“cooking pot”（「鍋」）。</p>\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0486_pot.jpg\" alt=\"金屬和陶瓷烹飪鍋\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">金屬和陶瓷烹飪鍋 (Gary Todd, Israel Museum, CC0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:12\">JOB 41:12</a> （《和》41:20；以下註解摘自《〈約伯記〉手冊》（<em>A Handbook on The Book of Job</em> ））：這節經文第二行的字面意思是，「像吹著爐風的鍋和蘆葦」。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> 和<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 的譯文略有不同；和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:13\">JER 1:13</a> 一樣，「燒開的鍋」字面作「吹著爐風的鍋」，表明這口鍋底下的火苗被爐風吹得很旺，鍋裡的東西隨著溫度升高被煮開了。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 把「蘆葦」譯為“burning rushes”（「燃燒著的蘆葦」），而<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 形容從力威亞探鼻孔冒出來的煙就“like smoke from weeds burning under a pot”（「如鍋下燃燒的雜草冒出的煙」）。「雜草」比「蘆葦」一詞更加籠統。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 的翻譯與希伯來文本並不是非常貼近。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> 顯然是把力威亞探鼻孔裡冒出的煙比作「從用蘆葦燒開的鍋」中冒出的蒸汽。這個譯法比<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 或<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 更加貼近希伯來文本，但至於蘆葦是否確實是作者想表達的一部分，這就很難說了。整節經文更為合理的一種譯法是，「煙從牠的鼻孔冒出，就像從沸騰的鍋中冒出那樣。」</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps58:10\">PSA 58:10</a> （《和》58:9）：這節經文的希伯來文本特別難解。請參考《〈詩篇〉手冊》（<em>A Handbook on Psalms</em> ）第519頁。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:4\">MRK 7:4</a> 所論到的器皿是廚房用具，用來烹飪食物或盛食物。大多數現代譯本都將這裡的希臘文<em>chalkion</em> 譯為「鍋」（“pots”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> ）或「碗」（“bowls”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> ）。在許多語言中，這個詞最自然的對等詞是「金屬容器」或「壺」。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc7:3\">2MA 7:3</a> 中，希臘文<em>lebēs</em> 和<em>tēganon</em> 一起出現。<em>Lebēs</em> 似乎與沸騰的水有關，所以可譯為「釜」（“caldrons”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> ）或「水壺」（“kettles”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ）。<em>Tēganon</em> 是用來煎炸的器具。在這個語境中，這兩種器具都非常大，所以<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> 把<em>tēganon</em> 譯為“great pans”（「大平鍋」），而<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 譯為“huge pans”（「巨大的平鍋」）。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
